Two other trials included infants 23-48 weeks post-menstrual age, (0-80 days postnatal age) with complicated intra-abdominal infections. Clearance increased with increasing post-menstrual age, while volume of distribution and half-life decreased (see PRECAUTIONS, Pediatric Use and 

                              DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                           ).

                           Recommended Dosage in Patients with Severe Hepatic Impairment

For patients with severe hepatic impairment (Child-Pugh C), the metronidazole dose should be reduced by 50% (see CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY and PRECAUTIONS
                           ).
